{"id":645912168,"lang":"cpp","time":"1 month, 2 weeks","timestamp":1645437509,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"40 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/645912168/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Two Sum IV - Input is a BST","memory":"38.8 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\n * struct TreeNode {\n *     int val;\n *     TreeNode *left;\n *     TreeNode *right;\n *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}\n * };\n */\nclass Solution {\n    bool traverse(TreeNode *root, unordered_set<int> &m, int k)\n    {\n        if(root == NULL)\n            return false;\n        \n        if(m.count(k - root->val)) \n            return true;\n        \n        m.insert(root->val);\n        \n        return traverse(root->left, m, k) || traverse(root->right, m, k);\n    }\n    \n    public:\n    bool findTarget(TreeNode* root, int k) {\n        unordered_set<int> m;\n        \n        return traverse(root, m, k);\n    }\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"two-sum-iv-input-is-a-bst"}
